pan>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-7\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-7\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\">Mark, David M. \"Spatial representation: a cognitive view.\" <i>Geographical information systems: Principles and applications</i> 1 (1999): 81-89.</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-8\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-8\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\">Montello, Daniel R. \"Cognitive research in GIScience: Recent achievements and future prospects.\" <i>Geography Compass</i> 3.5 (2009): 1824-1840.</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-9\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-9\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\">Montello, Daniel R. \"Cognitive geography.\" (2009).</span>\n</li>\n</ol></div>\n<h3><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Further_reading\">Further reading</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Cognitive_geography&amp;action=edit&amp;section=6\" title=\"Edit section: Further reading\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h3>\n<ul><li>Downs, Roger M., and David Stea. (1977). <i>Maps in Minds: Reflections on Cognitive Mapping.</i> HarperCollins Publishers.</li>\n<li>Kitchin, Rob, and Scott Freundschuh, eds. (2000). <i>Cognitive Mapping: Past, Present, and Future.</i> Vol. 4. Psychology Press.</li>\n<li><a href=\"/wiki/David_Mark_(scientist)\" title=\"David Mark (scientist)\">Mark, David M</a>., et al. (1999). \"<a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://www.researchgate.net/profile/Barbara_Tversky/publication/220649951_Cognitive_models_of_geographical_space/links/0fcfd507d7e6f5abdb000000.pdf\">Cognitive models of geographical space</a>.\" <i>International Journal of Geographical Information Science</i> 13.8: 747-774.</li>\n<li><a href=\"/wiki/Daniel_R._Montello\" title=\"Daniel R. Montello\">Montello, Daniel R.</a> (2009). \"Cognitive geogr